INTRODUCTION
1.
Aeromodelling is one of the finest hobbies, which is very popular worldwide among
people of various age groups. It has often been the starting point of many pilot/ aero-
nautical careers. The aim of including aeromodelling in the NCC curriculum is to enhance
the interest among NCC cadets. If taken on the right lines, it can be extremely thrilling for
all, as by constructing the models by one’s own hands, it will make understanding of various
principles of flight and problems of construction etc. very easy, apart from providing great
personal satisfaction to the aero- modeler.
2.
There are quite a number of variants of aero models, which are classified according to
the role and utility of the particular type, the main types are described in the following parts.
3.
International competitions for different aeromodelling events are organized at various
levels across the world. In India the apex body for aeromodelling is known as 'All India
Aeromodellers Association' which conducts Pan-Indian competitions in various events.
Gradually, aeromodelling is becoming increasingly popular all over the country specially
amongst the NCC Airwing Cadets.
PREVIEW
The lecture will be conducted in following
parts:-
